{{#> base title='photographer'}}
  {{#*inline 'content'}}

    {{> header subtitle='photographer.'}}

    <div class='o-container'>
      <div class='o-row'>
        <div class='o-col-oneWhole'>
          <img src='images/tcp-sclater.jpg' style='max-width: 100%; height: auto;' alt='Photograph by Cole Peters, from Sclater Street, East London, 2015'>
          <small class='s-gray-700'>
            Sclater Street, East London; 2015
          </small>
        </div>

        <div class='o-col-oneWhole _lg-o-col-twoThirds u-mt4'>
          <p class='s-h3'>
            Ever since my father put an Olympus Stylus Epic into my then-adolescent hands, I have been a devout practitioner of photography.
          </p>
          <p>
            I am a street and documentary photographer at heart, driven to capture both pseudo-fictional stories and factual events. I shoot strictly in black and white, a practice held dear from my days of developing and printing my own images in a home darkroom.
          </p>
          <p>
            I have spent nearly every weekend of 2015 on the streets of London and other locations in Europe, capturing spontaneous moments in an ongoing series of images which seek to engage the viewer in the creation of spontaneous narratives.
          </p>
          <p>
            A book of photographs is currently being developed for self-publication 2016.
          </p>

          <h2 class='s-h3 u-mt4'>
            Recent and ongoing work
          </h2>

          <dl>
            <dt><a href='images-pour-rien.html'>Images Pour Rien</a></dt>
            <dd>My first book of photographs, comprising a year’s worth of images of people, places, and presences.</dd>
            
            <dt class='u-mt3'><a href='https://blog.colepeters.com/submitted/'>Submission for LensCulture VSAs 2015</a></dt>
            <dd>A blog entry, detailing the photographs and words I submitted to the LensCulture Visual Storytelling Awards, 2015.</dd>

            <dt class='u-mt3'><a href='https://colepeters.exposure.co/'>Photo essays, on Exposure</a></dt>
            <dd>An ongoing series of photo-essays reside over at my little home on Exposure. I try to add new stories at least once every month.</dd>
            
            <dt class='u-mt3'><a href='https://cole.vsco.co'>My VSCO Grid</a></dt>
            <dd>My most recently-published photographs can be found on my VSCO Grid, along with images shot on mobiles over the past couple years. New images are added on a weekly basis (sometimes more often).</dd>

            <dt class='u-mt3'>Elsewhere</dt>
            <dd>You can also find my photographs on <a href='https://www.flickr.com/photos/colepetersphoto/'>Flickr</a>, including some less-recent work dating back to 2008. A mix of professional and personal/casual photos can be found on <a href='https://instagram.com/colepetersphoto'>my Instagram</a>.</dd>
          </dl>

          {{>footer}}

        </div>
      </div>
